&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Contracts Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full Time, Exempt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Hybrid-Reston, VA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: &lt;/strong&gt;CEO&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you highly organized, detail-oriented, and experienced in construction contracts? We&#39;re seeking a Contract &amp;amp; Procurement Administrator to help streamline and modernize contract management across our growing group of companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity to work directly with company leadership, legal counsel, purchasing teams, and key stakeholders to improve contract processes, reduce risk, and implement innovative solutions—including AI and automation tools—to drive efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Disclaimer:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; The following description has been designed to indicate the general nature and essential responsibilities of work performed by employees within this classification. It is not a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities, and qualifications required.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, update and maintain client proposal and vendor contract templates for 3 operating businesses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with attorney to understand legal implications of typical contract language and proposed revisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate closely with company leadership, purchasing team, vendor relationship team, third party attorney and different internal buyers to create and improve contract related processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;focus on expediting contract administration, negotiation and execution process while maintaining critical controls to protect company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strike balance between contract language being reasonable and not overwhelming/business friendly while protecting organization&#39;s best interests (especially on sensitive clauses).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement automation and AI into review processes to increase efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing familiarity with construction contract language implications (in Virginia, DC and Maryland)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3+ years of relevant experience managing the full lifecycle of construction contracts and procurement processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong administrative skills in programs such as Microsoft Word used to negotiate contract language&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Salary + Yearly Bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Holidays and Vacation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health, Vision, and Dental Insurance plus additional voluntary plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K with company match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company phone, computer,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Muller Inc is an Equal Opportunity Employer and makes hiring decisions solely on the basis of merit&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a crew of 2-3 laborers on a daily basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and complete work such as silt fence installation, hydroseeding, underdrain installation, manhole punch work, bond release items, asphalt patching and crack sealing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate mini-excavators and skid steers to perform daily job functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete daily paperwork including but not limited to daily job tickets, time sheets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trench/Excavate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load and unload construction materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respectfully Communicate directly with Client Representatives, Superintendents, and Project Managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Super Silt Fence, Silt fence, seeding, punch work, or under drain experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid Driver’s license&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience driving a truck with trailer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift 50lbs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eligible for employment in the United States&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years’ construction or landscaping experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Bobcats and/or mini excavator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Silt fence or under drain experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable transportation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employee must be physically fit to perform manual labor in all types of environments and conditions, including heavy lifting (up to 50 lbs.).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regularly required to sit and stand, must be able to use hands to fingers, handle or feel and verbally communicate and listen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other physical requirements include walking, climbing or balancing and stooping, kneeling, crouching or crawling. Specific vision abilities required by the position include distance vision, color vision, peripheral vision, depth perception and the ability to adjust focus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive hourly rate based on experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical/Dental/Vision/Life Insurance/Short Term Disability/Accident/Critical Illness/Hospital Confinement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Time Off&lt;/li&gt;
