&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Muller is a full-service sitework contractor based in Northern Virginia, delivering sustainable civil construction services across Maryland, Virginia, and DC through a technology-driven, systems-based approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled Recruiter to join our operations. This role requires at least 3 years of experience in construction, skilled trades, or industrial recruiting, with staffing experience preferred and Spanish and English fluency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Recruiter will manage full-cycle recruiting for craft and construction professionals, qualify candidates, attending industry and boots on the ground events, support onboarding, and serve as a key liaison between field operations and HR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is a part of a high-performing, established recruiting team with strong systems, resources, and leadership support. We are looking to add individuals who are proactive, detail-oriented, and driven to deliver results in a fast-paced, growth-focused environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Disclaimer:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; The following description has been designed to indicate the general nature and essential responsibilities of work performed by employees within this classification. It is not a comprehensive inventory of all duties, responsibilities, and qualifications required.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Field Recruiting (Skilled Trades, Construction)- On-site position with travel requirements; this is not a remote role. &amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;**Flexible scheduling within established business needs**&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source and connect with hourly trades talent through job boards, referrals, events, and local networks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong pipelines for high-volume and hard-to-fill field roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Screen candidates for skills, experience, and job fit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Partner with Field Teams&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Ops, PMs, and field leaders to understand staffing needs and timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay ahead of hiring demands and flag any gaps early&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share what you’re seeing in the market (availability, pay trends, hiring challenges)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Field Presence &amp;amp; Events&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the company at job fairs, trade schools, and community events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help run proprietary hiring events and local recruiting efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with workforce programs and trade partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Candidate Experience&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the main point of contact for candidates through the process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep communication clear and timely from screen to hire to onboarding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make sure candidates have a smooth, positive experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Admin &amp;amp; Tracking&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep systems and trackers updated (apps, pipelines, hires, metrics)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay compliant with hiring policies and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track basic metrics like time-to-fill and hiring results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
